  "text": "Note that the preferred choices for both the uncoordinated and coordinated strategies are clear from examples 2 and 5. In case of uncoordinated strategies, example 2 shows that the random access CDMA supports order of magnitude higher load than random access FDMA and in case of coordinated strategies, example 5 shows that coordinated FDMA is clearly a better choice over coordinated TDMA. Therefore, in this section we will not consider random access FDMA and coordinated TDMA, except when we compare energy optimal solutions. Interested readers can refer to [CITATION_1] for a detailed discussion on the optimal power TDMA results. Instead, our main focus in this section will be on random access CDMA, coordinated FDMA and SIC in various regimes of interest.",
